<li><a href="http://www.humanities.mq.edu.au/Ockham/y64l10.html" class="external text" title="http://www.humanities.mq.edu.au/Ockham/y64l10.html" rel="nofollow">Max Weber: On Capitalism As above, but on capitalism</a></li>
<li><a href="http://socserv2.mcmaster.ca/soc/courses/soc2r3/weber/weberidx.htm" class="external text" title="http://socserv2.mcmaster.ca/soc/courses/soc2r3/weber/weberidx.htm" rel="nofollow">Some of Weber concepts in the form of a list</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.faculty.rsu.edu/~felwell/Theorists/Weber/Whome.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.faculty.rsu.edu/~felwell/Theorists/Weber/Whome.htm" rel="nofollow">Max Weber's HomePage "A site for undergraduates"</a></li>
<li><a href="http://mises.org/journals/jls/18_1/18_1_1.pdf" class="external text" title="http://mises.org/journals/jls/18_1/18_1_1.pdf" rel="nofollow">Mises versus Weber on Bureaucracy and Sociological Method</a> by William P. Anderson</li>
<li><a href="http://www.econ.nyu.edu/cvstarr/seminars/callahan.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.econ.nyu.edu/cvstarr/seminars/callahan.pdf" rel="nofollow">Reconciling Weber and Mises on Understanding Human Action</a> by Gene Callahan</li>
</ul>
